{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019HLGVgiX6XYMADSFy385JM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you requested. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n### 1. All Migration Files (Chronological Order)\n\n1. `001_init.sql` - Initial database setup\n2. `002_auth_sessions.sql` - Authentication sessions table\n3. `003_tier_to_amount.sql` - Tier to amount mapping\n4. `004_match_id_index.sql` - Match ID indexing\n5. `005_closecall_rounds.sql` - Close Call rounds table\n6. `006_closecall_candles.sql` - Close Call price candles cache\n7. `007_round_entries.sql` - Round entries table\n8. `008_user_transactions.sql` - Player transaction history ledger\n9. `009_transactions.sql` - Transactions table\n10. `010_event_queue.sql` - Event queue table\n11. `011_referral.sql` - Referral system tables\n12. `012_referral_claim_retry.sql` - Referral claim retry support (MOST RECENT)\n\n### 2. Most Recent Migration (012_referral_claim_retry.sql)\n\nThis migration adds retry support and concurrent claim guards to the referral claims system:\n- Adds 'error' as a valid claim status for retryable transient failures\n- Adds `retry_count` column to track failed claim attempts\n- Creates a partial unique index `idx_referral_claims_wallet_active` to prevent concurrent active claims for the same wallet (only one claim can be in pending/processing/error status at a time)\n\n### 3. Migration 008_user_transactions.sql (Player Transaction History)\n\nThis migration creates the `user_transactions` table for storing player transaction history:\n- **Table**: `user_transactions` with columns: `id`, `wallet`, `game`, `match_id`, `event`, `amount_lamports`, `tx_sig`, `created_at`\n- **Purpose**: One row per user-visible game event (join, win, loss, refund), used by the profile transactions API\n- **Indexes**: \n  - `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` - for paginated history by wallet\n  - `idx_user_tx_match_id` - for dedup/lookup by match_id\n- **Idempotency**: Unique constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` to prevent duplicate entries"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa94e491-d3b8-48ec-9244-f434c72362a9","uuid":"bbc59f88-91a4-4d22-aef6-dee10f7f7840","timestamp":"2026-03-31T14:03:47.826Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all migration SQL files in the backend submodule. I need to see:\n1. The list of all migration files in backend/migrations/ (or services/backend/migrations/ or similar)\n2. The content of the most recent migration file\n3. The content of migration 008_user_transactions.sql (if it exists)\n\nThe repo root is /workspaces/rng-utopia and backend is a git submodule at /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/\n\nBe thorough - check both backend/ and services/backend/ paths.","agentId":"adce35dc1e293dd79","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you requested. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n### 1. All Migration Files (Chronological Order)\n\n1. `001_init.sql` - Initial database setup\n2. `002_auth_sessions.sql` - Authentication sessions table\n3. `003_tier_to_amount.sql` - Tier to amount mapping\n4. `004_match_id_index.sql` - Match ID indexing\n5. `005_closecall_rounds.sql` - Close Call rounds table\n6. `006_closecall_candles.sql` - Close Call price candles cache\n7. `007_round_entries.sql` - Round entries table\n8. `008_user_transactions.sql` - Player transaction history ledger\n9. `009_transactions.sql` - Transactions table\n10. `010_event_queue.sql` - Event queue table\n11. `011_referral.sql` - Referral system tables\n12. `012_referral_claim_retry.sql` - Referral claim retry support (MOST RECENT)\n\n### 2. Most Recent Migration (012_referral_claim_retry.sql)\n\nThis migration adds retry support and concurrent claim guards to the referral claims system:\n- Adds 'error' as a valid claim status for retryable transient failures\n- Adds `retry_count` column to track failed claim attempts\n- Creates a partial unique index `idx_referral_claims_wallet_active` to prevent concurrent active claims for the same wallet (only one claim can be in pending/processing/error status at a time)\n\n### 3. Migration 008_user_transactions.sql (Player Transaction History)\n\nThis migration creates the `user_transactions` table for storing player transaction history:\n- **Table**: `user_transactions` with columns: `id`, `wallet`, `game`, `match_id`, `event`, `amount_lamports`, `tx_sig`, `created_at`\n- **Purpose**: One row per user-visible game event (join, win, loss, refund), used by the profile transactions API\n- **Indexes**: \n  - `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` - for paginated history by wallet\n  - `idx_user_tx_match_id` - for dedup/lookup by match_id\n- **Idempotency**: Unique constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` to prevent duplicate entries"}],"totalDurationMs":22417,"totalTokens":30334,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1765,"cache_read_input_tokens":27976,"output_tokens":587,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1765},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
