{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RoFYvWECRNhCTf6UXtUYrP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a comprehensive report with the findings:\n\n## Database Patterns Report - RNG Utopia Backend\n\nBased on my analysis of the backend database code, here's a comprehensive breakdown of the database patterns:\n\n### Key File Locations\n\n1. **Main DB Module**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` (977 lines)\n2. **DB Configuration**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db-config.ts` (37 lines)\n3. **Migration Runner**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/migrate.ts` (158 lines)\n4. **Migrations Directory**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/` (12 .sql files)\n\n---\n\n## 1. DB Connection Setup Pattern\n\n**Engine**: PostgreSQL via the `postgres` package (raw SQL, not ORM)\n\n**Connection initialization** (in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl, sql);\n```\n\n**Schema handling** (`db-config.ts`):\n- `loadDbSchemaFromEnv()` — reads `DB_SCHEMA` env var, defaults to `\"public\"`\n- `applyDbSchemaToUrl()` — injects PostgreSQL `search_path` option into the connection URL\n- Allows switching between multiple schemas without code changes\n\n**Factory function** (`db.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string, _txSql?: any): Db {\n  const sql: any = _txSql ?? postgres(databaseUrl);\n  const _isOwner = !_txSql;  // Track if we own the connection\n  return { ... }\n}\n```\n- Accepts optional pre-existing SQL client for transaction nesting\n- Returns typed `Db` interface with all query methods\n\n---\n\n## 2. Query Function Structure Pattern\n\nThe `Db` interface defines 40+ typed query methods with consistent patterns:\n\n**Read-only queries** (return typed results):\n```typescript\ngetRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>\ngetRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>\ngetTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>\n```\n\n**Write queries** (insert/update):\n```typescript\ninsertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>\nupdateRoundPhase(pda: string, newPhase: RoundPhase, updates?: Partial<...>): Promise<Round>\ninsertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>\n```\n\n**Batch operations**:\n```typescript\ninsertTransactions(params: InsertTransactionParams[]): Promise<void>\ngetLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas: string[], eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<Map<string, OperatorEvent>>\n```\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- Each query is a typed async method\n- Template strings with parameterized queries (automatic SQL injection prevention)\n- Normalization functions convert raw DB values (BIGINT→number, JSONB→parsed objects)\n- Error messages are descriptive (e.g., \"Invalid phase transition: created → blue\")\n\n**Data normalization pattern**:\n```typescript\nfunction normalizeRound(row: Round): Round {\n  return {\n    ...row,\n    amount_lamports: Number(row.amount_lamports),  // BIGINT → number\n    entries: Array.isArray(row.entries)\n      ? row.entries.map(e => ({ player: e.player, amountLamports: Number(e.amountLamports) }))\n      : null,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Migration Pattern\n\n**System overview** (`migrate.ts`):\n- Reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` directory\n- Applies them in order via a `_migrations` version table\n- Each migration runs in a transaction (all-or-nothing)\n- Idempotent: re-running skips already-applied files\n\n**CLI usage**:\n```bash\ntsx src/migrate.ts          # Run pending migrations\ntsx src/migrate.migrate status   # Show applied vs pending\n```\n\n**Migration files** (12 total):\n1. `001_init.sql` — `rounds` & `operator_events` (commit-reveal schema)\n2. `002_auth_sessions.sql` — JWT authentication\n3. `003_tier_to_amount.sql` — Schema evolution\n4. `004_match_id_index.sql` — Performance indexes\n5. `005_closecall_rounds.sql` — Separate table for oracle-resolved Close Call rounds\n6. `006_closecall_candles.sql` — Price candle cache\n7. `007_round_entries.sql` — JSONB entries field\n8. `008_user_transactions.sql` — Old schema (replaced by 009)\n9. `009_transactions.sql` — Player transaction history\n10. `010_event_queue.sql` — Async event processing\n11. `011_referral.sql` — Full referral system (codes, links, earnings, claims)\n12. `012_referral_claim_retry.sql` — Retry tracking for referral payouts\n\n**Example migration structure** (`001_init.sql`):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS rounds (\n  pda TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  game TEXT NOT NULL,\n  creator TEXT NOT NULL,\n  phase TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  entries JSONB,\n  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_rounds_phase ON rounds(phase);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Key Tables & Schemas\n\n**Core game tables**:\n- `rounds` — Commit-reveal coinflip + jackpot matches (shared, distinguished by `game` column)\n- `operator_events` — Audit log with JSONB payload storage\n- `closecall_rounds` — Pari-mutuel oracle-resolved rounds\n- `closecall_candles` — Price data cache\n\n**Auth tables**:\n- `auth_challenges` — Challenge-response JWT auth\n- `refresh_tokens` — Token refresh tracking\n\n**Referral system tables**:\n- `referral_codes` — One active code per wallet\n- `referral_links` — Immutable referrer→referee binding\n- `referral_earnings` — Per-game earnings tracking (one row per referee per round)\n- `referral_claims` — Async SOL payout tracking with status/retry\n- `referral_kol_rates` — Custom rates for key opinion leaders\n\n**Transaction history**:\n- `transactions` — Player tx history (deposits, payouts, refunds)\n- `event_queue` — Async event processing\n\n---\n\n## 5. Advanced Patterns\n\n**Phase transition guard** (enforces state machine):\n```typescript\nconst VALID_TRANSITIONS: Record<RoundPhase, readonly RoundPhase[]> = {\n  created: [\"locked\", \"expired\"],\n  locked: [\"settling\"],\n  settling: [\"settled\"],\n  settled: [],\n  expired: [],\n};\n\nfunction assertPhaseTransition(from: RoundPhase, to: RoundPhase): void {\n  const allowed = VALID_TRANSITIONS[from];\n  if (!allowed.includes(to)) throw new Error(`Invalid phase transition...`);\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction support** (for multi-step operations):\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency patterns**:\n```typescript\nON CONFLICT DO NOTHING  // insertTransaction, insertTransactions\nUNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  // referral_earnings\n```\n\n**Pagination with cursor**:\n```typescript\ngetTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number)\n// WHERE id < ${cursor} ORDER BY id DESC\n```\n\n**Aggregations for stats**:\n```typescript\ngetPendingBalance(wallet) — SUM of referrer_earned + referee_rebate minus completed claims\ngetReferralStats(wallet) — COUNT + SUM queries with JOINs for complex analytics\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe database architecture is a **clean, typed, manual SQL approach** using `postgres` package with:\n- **Factory pattern** for DB creation (supports transactions)\n- **Interface-driven design** (40+ type-safe query methods)\n- **Normalization layer** (handles BIGINT→number, JSONB→objects)\n- **Migration system** (numbered .sql files, version table, idempotent)\n- **State machine enforcement** (phase transitions guarded)\n- **Async/retry patterns** (event queue, claims with retry tracking)\n- **Pagination & aggregation** (cursor-based, complex stats queries)\n\nAll amounts stored in **lamports** (u64) to avoid floating point issues. Amounts converted to number (JavaScript) on retrieval."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"